  "prompt": "Does long distance relationship work for teen?",
  "response": "Long-distance relationships can be challenging for teenagers due to several factors:\n\nPros:\n- Can help develop communication skills\n- Technology makes staying connected easier\n- Can build trust and emotional intimacy\n- Good for learning relationship dynamics\n\nCons:\n- Limited physical interaction\n- High emotional stress\n- Difficult to maintain trust\n- Age-related maturity challenges\n- Time and distance constraints\n- Potential for jealousy and insecurity\n\nFactors for success:\n- Strong communication\n- Mutual trust\n- Clear expectations\n- Regular communication\n- Shared goals\n- Emotional maturity\n- Planning future meet-ups\n\nRecommendations:\n- Set realistic expectations\n- Use video calls/messages\n- Have trust\n- Maintain individual lives\n- Be honest\n- Consider age and maturity\n- Be prepared for potential challenges\n\nWhile some teen long-distance relationships work, many struggle due to emotional immaturity and life changes. Success depends on individual commitment and relationship dynamics.",
